The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on May 1, 2009. He discussed a variety of topics including the interagency review of Ali al-Marri, the detainees at Guantanamo, and upcoming events for the President. He also answered questions about the Supreme Court, the bank stress tests, and the H1N1 flu pandemic. Additionally, President Obama made a surprise appearance at the end of the briefing to announce the retirement of Justice David Souter from the Supreme Court and discuss the process for selecting a replacement.